postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

title: For Sale:  26.5mm Flare Pistol Outfit - German Suhl, Really Nice
postcontent:
Here's a very nice and complete setup featuring a 26.5mm flare pistol made by Suhl (East Germany). I believe this pistol is designated the LP-1 and it's a post war product that was made from the late 40's up through the early 60's. This will shoot any of 26.5mm flare, starburst or smoke rounds available at Sportsman's Guide, Military Shooters, UNAMMO, etc..

This is one of the nicest examples I've seen with most of it's original finish intact. There is a little wear around the muzzle and on the sharp edges from holster use but not much. Overall I'd say that at least 90% of the original finish remains. Many times with these the finish is badly worn or the pistol has been painted. So finding one with it's original factory finish in this good of shape is not the norm.

The bore is in great shape too with no rust or pitting and it functions perfectly including the rather unusual safety lever feature.

Also included is a correct East German military black leather holster in very good shape that has a shoulder carry strap and a matching leather lanyard for the pistol. Then there is a complete cleaning kit that includes a stiff bristle nylon brush for normal cleaning. A brass bristle brush for heavy duty cleaning, and a felt tip rod that fits the bore snuggly and eliminates the need for cleaning patches.

Finally there is a sub-caliber adapter that allows you to shoot any .22 Short, Long or Long Rifle ammo from the flare pistol safely which makes a great combination for emergency and survival situations. There is also another adapter for firing the less expensive 12 gauge flares that are sold by BASS PRO, most boating supply houses, and even at some Walmart's.

$300 with pick up in the Brandon area. You must be at least 21 to purchase this flare gun with the .22 adapter. I can ship for $16 to any non-restrictive state. I won't ship to AK, HI or CA, NY, NJ, CT, DC, MA or any other place where it is prohibited.
